# Bottom navigation by role

HAGEE (client) and HAGU (provider) use **different** bottom navs. Do not share one tab array for both.

## Single source of truth

All tab definitions live in `lib/app-navigation.ts`:

- `HAGEE_BOTTOM_NAV` ‚Äî client app
- `HAGU_BOTTOM_NAV` ‚Äî provider app
- `getBottomNavConfig(role)` ‚Äî pick the correct nav for the session role
- `shouldHideBottomNav(pathname)` ‚Äî hide nav on full-screen subflows

`AppBottomNav` only renders icons + calls `getBottomNavConfig`; it must not define tabs inline.

## HAGEE tabs

| Key | Label | Route |
|-----|-------|-------|
| home | Home | `/home` |
| explore | Explore | `/explore` |
| chat | Chat | `/chat` |
| profile | Profile | `/profile` |

Active tab: `hageeNavTabFromPathname(pathname)`

## HAGU tabs

| Key | Label | Route |
|-----|-------|-------|
| home | Home | `/discover` (provider home) |
| bookings | Bookings | `/bookings` |
| calendar | Calendar | `/calendar` |
| settings | Settings | `/settings` |

Active tab: `haguNavTabFromPathname(pathname)`

## Role separation

HAGEE and HAGU are separate route trees. Never render both audiences from one page.

- HAGEE: `/home`, `/explore`, `/chat`, `/profile`
- HAGU: `/discover`, `/bookings`, `/calendar`, `/settings`

`roleGuardRedirect()` in `lib/app-navigation.ts` enforces this in `app/(app)/layout.tsx`.

## When adding a tab or route

1. Update the correct array in `lib/app-navigation.ts` only (HAGEE or HAGU).
2. Extend the matching `*NavTabFromPathname` helper so the active state highlights correctly.
3. If the screen is a subflow (chat thread, refine, edit profile), add it to `shouldHideBottomNav`.
